loads/2025/03/Erik-Per-Sullivan-and-Frankie-Muniz-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Erik-Per-Sullivan-and-Frankie-Muniz-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Erik-Per-Sullivan-and-Frankie-Muniz-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Erik-Per-Sullivan-and-Frankie-Muniz-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> The forthcoming revival of <em>Malcolm In The Middle</em> has recast the part of Dewey, after the previous actor Erik Per Sullivan became the only main cast member not to return.</p><p> <a href="https://variety.com/2025/tv/news/malcolm-in-the-middle-revival-christopher-masterson-justin-berfield-dewey-recast-1236347654/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Variety</em></a> reports that Caleb Ellsworth-Clark, known for his work on TV show <em>Fargo</em> , will instead play the part of youngest of the family&#39;s siblings. Frankie Muniz is returning in the title role, with <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/bryan-cranston">Bryan Cranston</a> and Jane Kaczmarek also coming back as parents Hal and Lois.</p><p> Ellsworth-Clark&#39;s casting was announced along with Christopher Masterson and Justin Berfield, who are reprising the roles of Francis and Reese. Original Dewey actor Sullivan retired from acting in 2010, and according to Kaczmarek simply <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/what-happened-to-dewey-actor-from-malcolm-in-the-middle-finally-revealed-3779852">lost interest in the profession.</a></p><p> “He&#39;s well, he&#39;s very, very well…He did Malcolm for seven years, he started at seven, he ended at 14. He wasn&#39;t interested in acting, at all” she said in an interview last year. “He goes to school at a very prestigious American university that he&#39;s asked us all to be quiet about… I admire it because so many people think being in show business is the greatest thing in the world, it&#39;s not for everyone”. </p><blockquote class